EnMAP is a pushbroom-type imaging
spectrometer with a prism-based dualspectrometer instrument design covering the
420–2450-nm spectral range: a VNIR system(420–1000 nm) and a SWIR system (900–2450nm). 
The threshold requirements for the Signalto-noise ratio (SNR) are
• VNIR >500:1 (@495 nm)
• SWIR > 150:1 (@2200 nm)
and the spectral calibration uncertainty
• VNIR 0.5 nm
• SWIR 1 nm
The required radiometric calibration accuracy is 5
% and co-registration VNIR-SWIR < 20 % of a pixel.


https://enmap.git-pages.gfz-potsdam.de/GFZ_Tools_EnMAP_BOX/EnPT/doc/tutorial.html
